Yes, indeed!  How does one undermine or transcend nationalism? By promoting
internationalism. Although the European Union and United Nations are both weak
and imperfect organizations, they both promise to break the cycle of warfare
which has erupted sporadically but alltoo often as a result of nationalism.
I maintain that language is a crucial aspect of bringing international  
structures into effective operation.  An international language reduces 
nationalistic sentiment by its very nature. The EU is in a position to make
a rational cost-effective decision to adopt Esperanto. Perhaps they will bend
to the numbers-based argument to support English; but I promise that this is 
a politically loaded decision, which will not go down easily, if at all.
Neutrality is the key. English can be viewed as neutral in India, but not in
Europe. Neutrality is a rational position. Esperanto is neutral.

